This sample shows how to call NoDecoratorInPublicAsync with required parameters.

var client = new AccessClient().GetPublicOperationClient("1.0.0");

var result = await client.NoDecoratorInPublicAsync("<name>");

This sample shows how to call NoDecoratorInPublic with required parameters.

var client = new AccessClient().GetPublicOperationClient("1.0.0");

var result = client.NoDecoratorInPublic("<name>");

This sample shows how to call NoDecoratorInPublicAsync with required parameters and parse the result.

var client = new AccessClient().GetPublicOperationClient("1.0.0");

Response response = await client.NoDecoratorInPublicAsync("<name>", new RequestContext());

JsonElement result = JsonDocument.Parse(response.ContentStream).RootElement;
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("name").ToString());

